	filename all_transitionsarrowsthick.eps
	width 75line%

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The first 4 bunch of transition are allowed by 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{JC}$
\end_inset

, as express in Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Frl"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 Interestingly new 5 transitions are opened by 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{S}$
\end_inset

 in violet.
 The 0-th order enable transition for 
\begin_inset Formula $f=i-1$
\end_inset

, and symmetrically 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{S}$
\end_inset

 enable new decay for 
\begin_inset Formula $f=i,i-2$
\end_inset

.
 The transitions due to the counter rotating Hamiltonian 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{R}$
\end_inset

 enable transitions for 
\begin_inset Formula $f=i+1,i-3$
\end_inset

.
 Of course 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 cannot be equal to 
\begin_inset Formula $i+1$
\end_inset

 for the energy conservation, implicitly written in the Fermi golden rule.
 The three thicker lines will be studied in more details in the next subsection.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:transitions"

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
